---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { brandName, companyLegalName, legalEmail, repoHref } from '../site.config';
---

<Layout
  title={`Privacy policy · ${brandName}`}
  description={`Privacy policy for the ${brandName} project website.`}
  current="privacy"
>
  <div class="wrap legal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="lead muted">
      This policy describes how <strong>{companyLegalName}</strong> handles information collected via the {brandName}
      project website. Last updated: <time datetime="2026-06-12">June 12, 2026</time>.
    </p>

    <h2>1) Scope</h2>
    <p>
      {brandName} is free and open-source software released under the Apache-2.0 license. This policy applies only to this
      informational website. The software itself runs entirely in your own infrastructure: it sends us no telemetry and
      phones no home.
    </p>

    <h2>2) Information we process</h2>
    <ul class="clean">
      <li>
        <strong>Operational website data:</strong> standard server logs needed for security, availability, and abuse
        prevention.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aggregate analytics data:</strong> if enabled, we use Plausible Analytics in cookieless mode to measure
        page usage trends. No personal profiles are built.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not run sales or contact forms here. Questions, bug reports, and feature requests are handled in the open on
      <a href={repoHref} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>, where your contributions are governed by
      GitHub's own privacy practices.
    </p>

    <h2>3) Analytics (Plausible scaffold)</h2>
    <p>
      When configured, this site loads Plausible Analytics with a domain-scoped script. Plausible is designed to work
      without cookies and without storing raw IP addresses.
    </p>
    <p>
      Analytics are disabled entirely when <code>PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN</code> is left unset in the build configuration.
    </p>

    <h2>4) How we use data</h2>
    <ul class="clean">
      <li>Keep the website secure and available.</li>
      <li>Improve website clarity and information architecture using aggregate page metrics.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5) Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      Server logs are retained only as long as needed for security and operational purposes. Aggregate analytics contain
      no personal identifiers.
    </p>

    <h2>6) Your choices and rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your jurisdiction, you may request access, correction, or deletion of any personal data associated
      with you. Because we collect no contact records here, in most cases there is nothing for us to hold.
    </p>

    <h2>7) Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, email <a href={`mailto:${legalEmail}`}>{legalEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
